I will be seen alongside some of Hip Hip’s greatest contributors and influencers in the upcoming book, ‘The Culture: Hip Hop and Contemporary Art in the 21st Century’

I can’t wait for the world to read this interview that I had the honor of doing with Asma Neem for the Baltimore Museum of Art. 

You may pre-order ‘The Culture’ book directly from the museum’s site (see link in my bio), and it will also be available worldwide via retailers including Barnes and Noble, Target and Amazon!

‘The Culture: Hip Hop and Contemporary Art in the 21st Century captures hip hop’s extraordinary influence on contemporary art and culture over the past two decades of its 50-year history. This comprehensive catalog features artworks from the exhibi
tion and contributions from more than 50 scholars, artists, curators, and arts leaders’ @baltimoremuseumofart #TheCultureBMA

2023 marks the 50th Anniversary of Hip Hop and ‘The Culture: Hip Hop & Contemporary Art in the 21st Century’ (written by Asma Naeem) is a book that captures the global influence of Hip Hop, “from the street to the runway,” and “the studio to the museum gallery.” The book also explores how Hip Hop continues to challenge structures of power, dominant cultural narratives, and political and social systems of oppression.

I am honored, as a deaf artist and child of the 1990’s- growing up in Sacramento, feeling the bass from Hip Hop music blasting in my mom’s car- to be included in this beautifully designed  book, alongside some of the greatest artists and innovators in music, fashion, and visual + performing arts.

‘The Culture’ is available worldwide where books are sold including Amazon, Target and directly on the artbma.org #shaheem #hiphop #theculture #kendricklamar #maliksayeed #california #TimelessVince

The National Association of the Deaf (NAD), LOVE SIGN (@lovesign.asl), and the @nfl  proudly announce that Super Bowl LVIII in Las Vegas, Nevada on February 11, 2024 will feature Deaf performers, Daniel Durant (@danielndurant), Anjel Piñero (@anjelpinero), and Shaheem Sanchez (@shaheem) during pregame festivities. Actor Daniel Durant, who starred in the Academy Award-winning movie “CODA,” will perform the National Anthem in ASL; actress and model Anjel Piñero will sign “America the Beautiful;” and Shaheem Sanchez, actor, dancer, and choreographer, will sign “Lift Every Voice and Sing.” Sanchez will also perform the ASL Halftime Show. The ASL pre-game performances and the ASL Halftime show will be produced in partnership with Alexis Kashar of LOVE SIGN and Howard Rosenblum of the NAD. Information on where to best watch these sign language performances will be shared when it becomes available. #SBLVIII
